issue_body:
I tried to validate the following:

    leaf iref {
        type identityref {
            base x;
            base y ;
        }

I got back:

keyword 'base' already given for the second base line.

YANG 1.1 supports multiple base statements for identityrefs, so why do I get the error? Is it just not yet supported or is there some other problem here?

Hi,

I compile dlib19.14 with CUDA.
When I try to use the exemple "dnn_face_recognition_ex.cpp", I have a crash of my application without errors and logs. I use QT 5.9

This crash appears  when I try to define the anet_type net
When I compile dlib without CUDA, it works fine


Here the code : 
```

#include <QCoreApplication>
#include <QTime>
