If the server is configured with NTLM only, the first response will be WWW-Authenticate: NTLM, and this is not handled by the module because it recognizes "negotiate" only. But this is a pity because the code is already there to handle NTLM. Suggest refactor the code to pass "_package" as a parameter to _retry_using_http_Negotiate_auth and do something like
```
    def _response_hook(self, r, **kwargs):
        if r.status_code == 401:
            if 'negotiate' in r.headers.get('WWW-Authenticate', '').lower():
                return self._retry_using_http_Negotiate_auth(r, 'Negotiate', kwargs)
            if 'ntlm' in r.headers.get('WWW-Authenticate', '').lower():
                return self._retry_using_http_Negotiate_auth(r, 'NTLM', kwargs)
```
Then it will work.

